{
  "_resourceType": "trigger",
  "id": "ba78d94d-8180-48ae-bbc9-b6ae8abd56e1",
  "_index": 0,
  "symbol": "trigger_fight",
  "prefabId": "",
  "name": "Fight",
  "notes": "Use hashtags (#MyVar and vars set to display certain ASCII values (like 97 for a) and thus changeable names. Kind of a pain in the butt. Use $MyVar to display the number beside the letter.\nAlternatively, create some way to call stored strings; if you only have 16 attacks then a simple switch statement depending on var stored number would work fine.\nIn actual game boy game asm I have seen tables used, so could alter the engine instead..\nWith the new update to make updating/replacing tiles easier and able to choose different tilesets for them, could use a custom tileset for a-z that's easy to remember (so a is now 1 and z 26) and that would make storing names much less painful.\nIt also opens up more possibilities for more monsters, storing them as new tilesets perhaps\n\nAlternatively and easier for moves, just make a new menu for each monster, if you don't have that many of 'em.",
  "x": 2,
  "y": 14,
  "width": 8,
  "height": 1,
